1. INTERPRETATION.

(a) "Party" shall mean any of the persons, firms, or corporations who have signed this Agreement;
(b) "Agreement" shall refer to this written document and any amendments thereto duly executed by all Parties;
(c) "Services" shall signify the services or goods provided by one Party to another as outlined in Schedule A hereto;
(d) "Fees" shall denote the amount payable for said Services, as stated in Schedule B hereto;
(e) "Term" shall refer to the period commencing on the Effective Date and ending on the Termination Date, unless earlier terminated by either Party with written notice.

