In addition, while each Party acknowledges its responsibility for the performance of its obligations under this Agreement, it is recognized that certain aspects of the Services may depend on factors outside the control of either Party (the "Force Majeure Events"). In such cases, the non-performing Party shall be excused from performance to the extent that the Force Majeure Event prevents it from fulfilling its obligations under this Agreement. The Party affected by a Force Majeure Event shall promptly notify the other of the existence and nature of the event, and both Parties agree to work cooperatively to minimize any disruption to the completion of the Services.
